The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, August 09, 2004 				 Triple benefit for ladies 
																								birla sun life Insurance has unveiled Ladyguard plan, which offers triple benefits of a life cover, payments at regular intervals and critical illness, accidental death and dismemberment benefit.																								It is a money-back plan with minimum guaranteed investment returns at 3 per cent per annum on the premiums, net of all policy fees and charges.																								Any woman between 20-35 years can buy this plan. One has to pay premiums for a period of 20 years but cash withdrawals are allowed anytime after three years. A sum equal to 20 per cent of the face amount is transferred into the holding account every five years and is available for withdrawal.																								The plan provides the option of three investment funds  Protector, Builder and Enhancer. One can switch between these options anytime after the first year and one switch is allowed free every year.																								In the event of death, the face-value amount of the cover along with the policy fund is paid to the nominee. On survival till maturity, the money is paid to the policyholder. 																								Under the critical illness benefit, the plan provides cover against primary, specific illnesses, pregnancy complications and congenital anomalies in a new-born child. The eligible amount under the benefit is payable if the insured or the new-born, as applicable, is diagnosed with one of the illnesses or conditions covered under this rider. But the insured has to survive for a period of at least 30 days from the date of diagnosis to get the benefit.																								The benefits under the accidental death and dismemberment cover will be paid wherever applicable.																								The premiums paid are eligible for tax benefits under Sections 88 and 80D and the benefits received under the plan are eligible for tax benefits under Section 10(10D) of the Income Tax Act.					 CHANDRALEKHA TULAL
